The paper proposes a new representation learning model for heterogeneous graphs in the biomedical domain. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories, as it proposes a new approach for learning node embeddings. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on biomedical entity classification, compound-gene bioactivity prediction, and biomedical information retrieval tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Databases (cs.DB), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
